  "texts": [
    "It compresses long, information-rich contexts into a small number of continuous prompt vectors, which are then used for QA.",
    "Unlike GIST, which compresses low-information texts of around 30 tokens focused on questions and instructions, ICAE can handle detailed contexts.",
    "The question itself remains uncompressed, and the answer is generated based on the compressed context and the uncompressed question.",
    "Since the decoder is frozen, the compression tokens can be used directly with the original LLM without fine-tuning.",
    "ICAE compresses up to 512 tokens into 32, 64, or 128 continuous vectors, achieving compression ratios between 4x and 16x."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}